        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 7:32PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 732 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Boulder, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Radersburg.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
